1
00:00:02,800 --> 00:00:04,990
Don't worry.

2
00:00:04,990 --> 00:00:07,360
Making up is the easiest part.

3
00:00:07,360 --> 00:00:09,130
Get off.

4
00:00:09,130 --> 00:00:10,970
Don't touch me!

5
00:00:10,970 --> 00:00:12,900
Ouch!

6
00:00:14,280 --> 00:00:18,430
You're the one who let me into your room.

7
00:00:18,430 --> 00:00:21,180
- Stop!
- Quit resisting already.

8
00:00:21,850 --> 00:00:23,640
Stop, please!

9
00:00:23,640 --> 00:00:25,670
Sui.

10
00:00:27,260 --> 00:00:29,080
Get off of her.

11
00:00:32,210 --> 00:00:34,580
You, again?

12
00:00:34,580 --> 00:00:37,490
This is between me and Sui. Get out!

13
00:00:37,490 --> 00:00:38,650
You get out.

14
00:00:38,650 --> 00:00:40,440
Shut up!

15
00:00:40,440 --> 00:00:42,410
Quit getting in my way!

16
00:00:42,410 --> 00:00:46,440
Woah, hey, ouch!

17
00:00:46,440 --> 00:00:49,260
Let me go! Stop!

18
00:00:49,260 --> 00:00:52,210
You broke something!

19
00:00:52,210 --> 00:00:54,870
I'm telling my mom!

20
00:00:54,870 --> 00:00:57,100
Ow, ouch!

21
00:00:58,290 --> 00:01:01,500
Get lost. If you don't, I'm calling the cops.

22
00:01:01,500 --> 00:01:05,920
What? But Sui was my fiancée!

23
00:01:08,970 --> 00:01:11,340
Why?

24
00:01:12,610 --> 00:01:14,210
Open up!

25
00:01:14,210 --> 00:01:16,200
I said, open the door!

26
00:01:16,200 --> 00:01:18,820
O-Oops, I left my phone in there.

27
00:01:18,820 --> 00:01:22,160
I need it for work! Please?

28
00:02:40,040 --> 00:02:41,760
Are you hurt?

29
00:02:43,750 --> 00:02:45,570
No.

30
00:02:47,210 --> 00:02:50,220
You've saved me, again.

31
00:02:51,370 --> 00:02:54,550
I'm sorry for roping you into my trouble.

32
00:02:54,550 --> 00:02:57,390
You don't need to apologize.

33
00:02:58,870 --> 00:03:00,730
No, I...

34
00:03:03,730 --> 00:03:06,580
That man, he was...

35
00:03:10,310 --> 00:03:12,320
Don't force yourself to speak.

36
00:03:12,320 --> 00:03:14,400
Take it easy for the night.

37
00:03:15,820 --> 00:03:19,510
If you're anxious, I can stay here with you.

38
00:03:22,840 --> 00:03:24,760
Thank you.

39
00:03:25,790 --> 00:03:29,360
I'll be fine.

40
00:03:44,000 --> 00:03:45,500
Huh?

41
00:03:46,430 --> 00:03:49,330
Why do you keep avoiding me?

42
00:03:55,420 --> 00:03:58,460
If you're going to ignore me...

43
00:04:04,630 --> 00:04:07,290
Let's just die together!

44
00:04:29,990 --> 00:04:32,170
Takizawa?

45
00:04:32,170 --> 00:04:34,370
Good morning.

46
00:04:34,370 --> 00:04:37,730
Could I ask a work related question?

47
00:04:42,910 --> 00:04:44,050
Good morning.

48
00:04:44,050 --> 00:04:46,020
Morning.

49
00:04:49,740 --> 00:04:51,290
- Good morning.
- Morning.

50
00:04:51,290 --> 00:04:52,900
Morning.

51
00:04:57,780 --> 00:04:59,280
Have some tea.

52
00:05:03,000 --> 00:05:06,730
What happened? Is everything okay?

53
00:05:08,690 --> 00:05:13,450
Why did you turn him down?

54
00:05:13,450 --> 00:05:15,030
Huh?

55
00:05:15,770 --> 00:05:19,820
Himukai came to make amends, didn't he?

56
00:05:21,240 --> 00:05:23,440
How do you know about that?

57
00:05:26,630 --> 00:05:30,150
Because I convinced him to.

58
00:05:32,040 --> 00:05:33,600
What?

59
00:05:34,740 --> 00:05:36,260
Wh-What the...

60
00:05:36,260 --> 00:05:39,680
I have the perfect plan.

61
00:05:39,680 --> 00:05:43,510
Whether you go through with it or not is up to you.

62
00:05:43,510 --> 00:05:47,450
I'll do anything to get Sui back.

63
00:05:47,450 --> 00:05:51,840
Great. Then let's get married.

64
00:05:57,280 --> 00:05:59,000
What?

65
00:05:59,000 --> 00:06:04,200
I won't ask for love.
I just want the status as your wife.

66
00:06:04,200 --> 00:06:08,630
And how would that help me?

67
00:06:09,760 --> 00:06:12,730
Let me finish.

68
00:06:14,620 --> 00:06:17,730
If we get married,

69
00:06:17,730 --> 00:06:21,920
I'll turn a blind eye to all your affairs.

70
00:06:21,920 --> 00:06:27,470
You can keep Sui as a mistress,

71
00:06:27,470 --> 00:06:30,770
and stay with her forever.

72
00:06:32,600 --> 00:06:34,250
I see your point now.

73
00:06:34,250 --> 00:06:39,870
Not many wives are so allowing of mistresses.

74
00:06:39,870 --> 00:06:42,730
It's not a bad deal for you at all.

75
00:06:44,690 --> 00:06:49,790
Sui would prefer to stay with me, right?

76
00:06:49,790 --> 00:06:52,110
Of course.

77
00:06:52,110 --> 00:06:53,790
One more thing.

78
00:06:55,200 --> 00:06:57,190
Here.

79
00:06:59,720 --> 00:07:01,190
Huh?

80
00:07:03,750 --> 00:07:07,120
[Check-up diagnosis]

81
00:07:07,120 --> 00:07:09,970
No issues, whatsoever?

82
00:07:09,970 --> 00:07:13,760
I promise to bear a healthy heir for you.

83
00:07:13,760 --> 00:07:21,800
Just guarantee me the money
and position as your wife.

84
00:07:21,800 --> 00:07:26,390
Is this how all three of us can be happy?

85
00:07:26,390 --> 00:07:29,090
I didn't even think of this solution.

86
00:07:29,090 --> 00:07:31,990
You're so smart, Takizawa!

87
00:07:31,990 --> 00:07:34,330
Thank you!

88
00:07:34,330 --> 00:07:39,730
Once I'm pregnant with an heir,
your parents will have to accept me.

89
00:07:39,730 --> 00:07:41,430
Yeah, you're right.

90
00:07:41,430 --> 00:07:44,040
I'm all in on your plan!

91
00:07:44,790 --> 00:07:47,770
This is all for Sui's sake.

92
00:07:47,770 --> 00:07:50,520
Everything is for Sui, right?

93
00:07:50,520 --> 00:07:52,030
That's right.

94
00:07:54,820 --> 00:07:56,420
Takizawa...

95
00:08:02,180 --> 00:08:05,330
This is all for Sui.

96
00:08:41,430 --> 00:08:48,030
We had sex with no love, just for you.

97
00:08:48,710 --> 00:08:53,130
With this plan of mine,

98
00:08:53,130 --> 00:08:57,050
the three of us can all get what we want.

99
00:08:57,050 --> 00:09:00,730
To not agree to such ingenuity...

100
00:09:01,740 --> 00:09:04,640
Sui, are you sure you're feeling all right?

101
00:09:06,720 --> 00:09:09,210
Takizawa...

102
00:09:09,210 --> 00:09:13,110
You're crazy.

103
00:09:15,510 --> 00:09:18,820
I am doing this for your sake.

104
00:09:18,820 --> 00:09:23,630
- But you're suggesting we...
- Sui. You are infertile.

105
00:09:24,310 --> 00:09:26,060
Quit dreaming,

106
00:09:26,060 --> 00:09:28,870
and become Himukai's mistress already.

107
00:09:28,870 --> 00:09:34,230
It's the only way you'll find happiness.

108
00:09:38,370 --> 00:09:42,160
Contact Himukai, now.

109
00:09:42,160 --> 00:09:44,470
Excuse me.

110
00:09:44,470 --> 00:09:48,640
We are not seeing clients
with no appointments today.

111
00:09:48,640 --> 00:09:51,480
I've come here for Sui's sake.

112
00:09:51,480 --> 00:09:53,500
Otherwise, she'll never be happy.

113
00:09:53,500 --> 00:09:56,620
That has nothing to do with our business.

114
00:09:56,620 --> 00:09:58,230
What?

115
00:10:01,540 --> 00:10:06,310
Excuse me, we'll be needing
this meeting room soon.

116
00:10:06,310 --> 00:10:09,170
Yes, I was just on my way out.

117
00:10:18,380 --> 00:10:20,320
Sui.

118
00:10:20,320 --> 00:10:24,210
Charming them with your pity act, again?

119
00:10:24,210 --> 00:10:25,840
What?

120
00:10:26,500 --> 00:10:28,380
I remember when your parents passed,

121
00:10:28,380 --> 00:10:34,240
you played the "pathetic girl"
to get everyone on your side.

122
00:10:35,210 --> 00:10:37,790
Monou would never do such a thing.

123
00:10:37,790 --> 00:10:40,710
You'll come to understand soon enough.

124
00:10:45,380 --> 00:10:50,520
Anyone who stands in my way will see hell.

125
00:10:52,840 --> 00:10:55,480
I'll see you all again soon.

126
00:11:09,730 --> 00:11:11,980
Are you both all right?

127
00:11:13,640 --> 00:11:15,960
I'm fine.

128
00:11:18,280 --> 00:11:23,480
I'll brew you a cup of hot tea.

129
00:11:37,670 --> 00:11:42,930
Have I been blind this whole time?

130
00:11:42,930 --> 00:11:44,400
What?

131
00:11:46,640 --> 00:11:48,840
I had a fiancé.

132
00:11:49,510 --> 00:11:52,580
The man you saw the other day.

133
00:11:53,900 --> 00:11:55,430
Oh, him.

134
00:11:56,180 --> 00:11:59,970
Our engagement was called off
because of my... circumstances.

135
00:12:02,170 --> 00:12:07,050
But he wanted to do things over again.

136
00:12:07,050 --> 00:12:08,540
What?

137
00:12:08,540 --> 00:12:11,210
Of course, I turned him down.

138
00:12:13,740 --> 00:12:20,140
I couldn't forgive him.
I must be so narrow-minded.

139
00:12:33,020 --> 00:12:35,400
<i>Dear, stop this.</i>

140
00:12:35,400 --> 00:12:37,460
<i>Stop it!</i>

141
00:12:39,190 --> 00:12:41,540
You don't have to forgive him.

142
00:12:43,290 --> 00:12:44,850
What?

143
00:12:47,260 --> 00:12:50,760
If it hurts you to try and forgive,
then don't.

144
00:12:55,800 --> 00:12:58,660
You don't have to ignore your resentment.

145
00:13:00,350 --> 00:13:02,990
Even if you despise him...

146
00:13:02,990 --> 00:13:04,810
Even if you feel you're weak...

147
00:13:07,590 --> 00:13:10,700
Protecting your heart is your priority.

148
00:13:15,620 --> 00:13:17,610
Thank you.

149
00:13:17,610 --> 00:13:21,010
You've saved me once again.

150
00:13:32,120 --> 00:13:35,250
I did exactly as you said,

151
00:13:35,250 --> 00:13:38,230
and nothing worked out!

152
00:13:38,230 --> 00:13:41,120
I'm calling off our marriage.

153
00:13:41,120 --> 00:13:44,170
Don't panic, Himukai.

154
00:13:44,170 --> 00:13:46,300
Everything will work out just fine.

155
00:13:46,300 --> 00:13:50,480
Besides, a bright future awaits us.

156
00:14:04,510 --> 00:14:06,000
Wh-What?

157
00:14:07,870 --> 00:14:11,760
It's the heir you so desperately yearned for.

158
00:14:11,760 --> 00:14:15,430
I've granted one of your wishes, haven't I?

159
00:14:18,660 --> 00:14:20,660
No way...

160
00:14:21,420 --> 00:14:24,340
I'm on my way to the gynecologist now.

161
00:14:24,340 --> 00:14:27,770
So, don't worry about Sui, okay?

162
00:14:27,770 --> 00:14:32,730
I've made sure she'll contact you.

163
00:14:34,270 --> 00:14:37,400
And I can trust you on this one?

164
00:14:38,170 --> 00:14:42,370
Of course. Just leave it all to me.

165
00:14:46,600 --> 00:14:49,960
Hang on tight.

166
00:14:49,960 --> 00:14:52,060
I will!

167
00:14:52,060 --> 00:14:54,360
We're veering starboard.

168
00:14:54,360 --> 00:14:57,580
Takizawa, the winds! They're strong!

169
00:15:00,830 --> 00:15:07,420
I thought Himukai only had
his riches going for him.

170
00:15:08,500 --> 00:15:12,500
His obsession for you has made him crazy.

171
00:15:12,500 --> 00:15:16,110
He's a dumb, nasty scumbag.

172
00:15:16,110 --> 00:15:19,190
What'd you ever see in him?

173
00:15:19,190 --> 00:15:20,940
Huh?

174
00:15:20,940 --> 00:15:25,300
Sorry. I forget you're weak to pushy guys.

175
00:15:25,300 --> 00:15:29,530
Still, glad you broke it off with him.

176
00:15:29,530 --> 00:15:30,900
Dinner's ready.

177
00:15:30,900 --> 00:15:33,150
Thanks.

178
00:15:33,150 --> 00:15:37,580
I'm partially to blame
for never seeing his faults either.

179
00:15:37,580 --> 00:15:39,900
There you go again.

180
00:15:39,900 --> 00:15:42,830
You're such an earnest gal, Sui.

181
00:15:42,830 --> 00:15:44,280
You think so?

182
00:15:44,280 --> 00:15:46,160
But enough about him.

183
00:15:46,160 --> 00:15:48,100
Here's to someone better.

184
00:15:48,100 --> 00:15:50,580
- Cheers.
- Cheers.

185
00:15:55,920 --> 00:15:58,150
With the new job under your belt,

186
00:15:58,150 --> 00:16:01,430
I know you'll find someone new.

187
00:16:02,550 --> 00:16:04,070
Someone new...

188
00:16:04,070 --> 00:16:06,280
What, found one already?

189
00:16:06,280 --> 00:16:08,380
No.

190
00:16:09,790 --> 00:16:14,200
Even if I did,
I don't think I'd take the initiative.

191
00:16:14,850 --> 00:16:16,460
I see.

192
00:16:19,320 --> 00:16:21,060
How's Mao?

193
00:16:31,080 --> 00:16:36,570
I was asking about his work ethic, but...

194
00:16:38,000 --> 00:16:39,830
Right, of course.

195
00:16:39,830 --> 00:16:42,110
Yeah, he's really dependable.

196
00:16:44,890 --> 00:16:48,350
Looks like you have found someone.

197
00:16:48,350 --> 00:16:50,890
Have not.

198
00:16:52,960 --> 00:16:54,700
What?

199
00:16:54,700 --> 00:16:57,280
So, there's nothing between you and Mao?

200
00:16:57,280 --> 00:16:59,750
Of course not.

201
00:17:00,620 --> 00:17:04,330
I think you're just his type, though.

202
00:17:04,330 --> 00:17:07,060
He's six years my junior.

203
00:17:07,060 --> 00:17:09,600
And my husband is four.

204
00:17:09,600 --> 00:17:11,620
It works for you because you're mature.

205
00:17:11,620 --> 00:17:15,570
Younger guys are great.
There's really no arguing, for one.

206
00:17:15,570 --> 00:17:19,650
And if he pisses you off,
it's easy to shrug off.

207
00:17:20,600 --> 00:17:22,010
When he's reliable,

208
00:17:22,010 --> 00:17:25,100
you can't help but be impressed
since he's younger.

209
00:17:25,100 --> 00:17:26,660
It's all great stuff.

210
00:17:26,660 --> 00:17:28,680
Thanks for sharing.

211
00:17:28,680 --> 00:17:30,940
Any time.

212
00:17:42,530 --> 00:17:45,430
Mao, want some coffee?

213
00:17:45,430 --> 00:17:46,990
Sure, thanks.

214
00:17:57,710 --> 00:18:00,380
I hope Monou will be all right...

215
00:18:05,920 --> 00:18:08,570
If anything crops up, I'll back her.

216
00:18:11,980 --> 00:18:17,850
Are you currently dating Monou?

217
00:18:17,850 --> 00:18:19,340
What?

218
00:18:20,430 --> 00:18:23,440
I'm sorry, never mind.

219
00:18:23,440 --> 00:18:27,020
It was an inappropriate question.

220
00:18:28,190 --> 00:18:30,070
It's fine.

221
00:18:30,070 --> 00:18:32,050
But why make that assumption?

222
00:18:34,230 --> 00:18:38,130
I'll be honest with you.

223
00:18:38,130 --> 00:18:42,220
I happened to see you two the other night.

224
00:18:48,660 --> 00:18:51,850
I see. Didn't realize someone was watching.

225
00:18:52,870 --> 00:18:57,030
I was just acting as a guardian of sorts.

226
00:18:57,030 --> 00:18:58,670
A guardian?

227
00:18:59,520 --> 00:19:04,700
She was self-destructing,
due to incidents at her previous workplace.

228
00:19:05,540 --> 00:19:08,620
I only helped her up
because she was blackout drunk.

229
00:19:11,610 --> 00:19:15,210
I see.

230
00:19:15,210 --> 00:19:17,500
Sounds like something you'd do.

231
00:19:19,410 --> 00:19:26,190
But for her to drink to her limits...
Things must have been rough.

232
00:19:28,350 --> 00:19:32,280
It might take a while
for her to fully recover.

233
00:19:33,230 --> 00:19:36,450
Nana, a coffee for me too, please.

234
00:19:36,450 --> 00:19:38,910
Shall we get to work?

235
00:19:41,270 --> 00:19:44,750
Aw, you always give Mao special treatment.

236
00:19:49,330 --> 00:19:51,570
I mean, I get it.

237
00:19:51,570 --> 00:19:55,230
Of course he's popular. He's so nice.

238
00:19:57,260 --> 00:20:02,420
Mizuno is also kind.
She has a strong sense of justice.

239
00:20:02,420 --> 00:20:06,430
Not to mention incredibly capable.

240
00:20:06,430 --> 00:20:10,030
She's actually taking the exam
to become a certified architect.

241
00:20:10,030 --> 00:20:12,630
She's a hard worker, that one.

242
00:20:12,630 --> 00:20:15,360
Considerate, too.

243
00:20:17,440 --> 00:20:20,340
She's a good girl, through and through.

244
00:20:26,240 --> 00:20:31,190
- See you all tomorrow.
- See you.

245
00:20:31,190 --> 00:20:34,150
Let's hold a welcome party
for Monou this Friday.

246
00:20:34,150 --> 00:20:35,390
Great idea.

247
00:20:35,390 --> 00:20:36,600
A party, for me?

248
00:20:36,600 --> 00:20:39,440
Yeah. Should we go to Vente?

249
00:20:39,440 --> 00:20:42,340
Great choice. Everything tastes great there.

250
00:20:42,340 --> 00:20:44,300
We might not get a reservation though.

251
00:20:44,300 --> 00:20:46,080
Fair point.

252
00:20:46,080 --> 00:20:48,050
It is a popular spot.

253
00:20:48,050 --> 00:20:49,950
Should we order take out instead?

254
00:20:49,950 --> 00:20:51,860
Sounds good to me.

255
00:20:51,860 --> 00:20:54,610
But where to eat it all?

256
00:20:54,610 --> 00:20:57,790
How about my place?

257
00:20:57,790 --> 00:21:00,110
We're neighbors, so it's convenient for us.

258
00:21:00,110 --> 00:21:03,000
What? You're neighbors?

259
00:21:03,000 --> 00:21:06,680
I'm staying in one of the company dorms.

260
00:21:06,680 --> 00:21:09,510
Oh yeah, they did mention an open room.

261
00:21:09,510 --> 00:21:11,620
Yes. I moved in there.

262
00:21:13,520 --> 00:21:15,740
I see.

263
00:21:16,460 --> 00:21:18,400
All right, I'm looking forward to it. See you.

264
00:21:18,400 --> 00:21:20,340
- See you tomorrow.
- Good bye.

265
00:21:20,340 --> 00:21:23,170
- Nana, you coming?
- Right.

266
00:21:23,170 --> 00:21:25,710
- See you both tomorrow.
- Bye.

267
00:21:25,710 --> 00:21:27,860
See you.

268
00:21:37,260 --> 00:21:39,000
What's the matter?

269
00:21:39,000 --> 00:21:41,160
I'm here about the child.

270
00:21:42,440 --> 00:21:44,730
Oh! I have it handled.

271
00:21:44,730 --> 00:21:48,780
I'll send you my diagnosis some other day.

272
00:21:51,050 --> 00:21:53,150
Don't lie.

273
00:21:53,150 --> 00:21:55,870
- What?
- There is no child.

274
00:21:57,750 --> 00:22:02,170
I had Mom look into your medical records.

275
00:22:02,170 --> 00:22:06,740
You didn't have a file
with this gynecologist.

276
00:22:06,740 --> 00:22:10,840
That pregnancy test
must've been someone else's.

277
00:22:10,840 --> 00:22:14,030
Why did you tell such an obvious lie?

278
00:22:15,850 --> 00:22:18,250
You really can't tell?

279
00:22:19,420 --> 00:22:22,780
It's because I love you, why else?

280
00:22:22,780 --> 00:22:26,460
Enough stupid lies!

281
00:22:26,460 --> 00:22:31,990
You said you only wanted money and status.

282
00:22:32,760 --> 00:22:35,460
I'm calling off this deal, marriage and all.

283
00:22:36,740 --> 00:22:38,870
Please, wait!

284
00:22:38,870 --> 00:22:41,730
I promise to birth your child.

285
00:22:41,730 --> 00:22:45,760
I'll handle Sui as well, so please!

286
00:22:45,760 --> 00:22:48,920
Please don't call off our marriage!

287
00:22:48,920 --> 00:22:51,520
How?

288
00:22:52,710 --> 00:22:54,010
What?

289
00:22:54,010 --> 00:22:57,250
I understand Sui better than anyone.

290
00:22:57,250 --> 00:23:00,520
We were together for seven years, after all.

291
00:23:02,390 --> 00:23:04,360
Sui won't agree to the schemes

292
00:23:04,360 --> 00:23:08,060
of a dirty woman like you.

293
00:23:10,320 --> 00:23:12,620
"Dirty"?

294
00:23:12,620 --> 00:23:17,240
If Sui won't return to me,

295
00:23:17,240 --> 00:23:21,710
then I'd much rather marry
someone Mom chooses, over you.

296
00:23:22,980 --> 00:23:27,350
Unbelievable...

297
00:23:30,320 --> 00:23:33,610
It's all her fault.

298
00:23:45,370 --> 00:23:47,780
I won't let my plan be ruined so easily.

299
00:23:47,780 --> 00:23:49,840
I felt like someone was following me home.

300
00:23:49,840 --> 00:23:52,790
- Following you?
- It's my first time presenting an idea.

301
00:23:52,790 --> 00:23:54,980
I think we can create a wonderful event.

302
00:23:54,980 --> 00:23:57,730
It's like when we first met.
Except, now we're reversed.

303
00:23:57,730 --> 00:23:59,900
Want to pick up where we left off that night?

